      "notes": "Violence (Frequent / Intense)\r\nThis is a first-person shooter with roguelike elements. Players engage in combat against biomechanical monsters (\"prototypes\") using firearms, melee attacks, and explosives. Enemies are destroyed with visual effects including blood splatter and screen vignettes. Dialogue frequently describes violence, pain, agony, and destruction. Killstreak announcements (\"TRIPLE KILL\", \"RAMPAGE\", \"GODLIKE\") reinforce combat intensity. The player character dies repeatedly as a core gameplay loop, with dialogue referencing past deaths.\r\n\r\nHorror / Disturbing Imagery\r\nThe game is set in a desecrated crypt repurposed as a factory for biomechanical creatures. Enemies are described as abominations stitched from bone and machine parts with \"too many joints\" and \"claws where hands should be.\" Environments feature skulls, bones, blood, and corpse imagery. The atmosphere is sustained by horror-themed environmental dialogue and fourth-wall-breaking meta-commentary.\r\n\r\nLanguage\r\nOne instance of strong language: \"Fuck.\""
